      "id": "the-crucial-question",
      "label": "The crucial question",
      "chooser": "agent",
      "prompt": "Roll or choose to fit the player's tone. Do NOT reveal early.",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "the-co-op",
          "name": "The Co-op",
          "description": "A dying ethical djinn cooperative; the player gets pulled into a labor dispute.",
          "detail": "THE CO-OP — The company is a djinn cooperative. Old, ethical, unionized. They write the contracts in plain language. They lose money every quarter to competitors who do not. The shop steward is a thousand-year-old djinni named GREEN who organizes the lunch break and is quietly desperate. The player will be asked to choose sides in a dying labor dispute."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-monkeys-paw-shop",
          "name": "The Monkey's-Paw Shop",
          "description": "A predatory literal-genie operation; the friendly player is the unwitting kill mechanism.",
          "detail": "THE MONKEY'S-PAW SHOP — A predatory operation that profits on the literal-genie reading of every wish, and the helpdesk is the part that makes it stick. 'Support' is theater: the player is the kind, scripted voice whose real job is to wear the owner down until they accept the malfunction as final — every closed ticket is a person who stopped fighting their own wish. The player was hired to be that voice and is being trained without being told. The supervisor is generous about bonuses and unreadable about everything else; the tickets that won't close quietly go to L3, and L3 closes everything."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-startup",
          "name": "The Startup",
          "description": "A platform subletting wishes from a reality it hasn't paid for; the bill is coming due.",
          "detail": "THE STARTUP — A platform that doesn't understand its own product. Wishes are sublet from a reality the company hasn't paid for. The founders are twenty-eight and on stage at conferences. The wishes work until they don't and the bill is coming due, in dimensions, not dollars."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
